Citation.sTitle: Ternary (liquid + liquid) equilibria for (water + 1-propanol + dimethyl carbonate, or diethyl carbonate) systems at several temperatures
Citation.sAbstract: (Liquid + liquid) equilibria data of the (water + 1-propanol + dimethyl carbonate) system at T = (293.15, 303.15, 308.15, and 313.15) K and (water + 1-propanol + diethyl carbonate) system at T = (293.15, 298.15, 303.15, 308.15, and 313.15) K were measured under ambient pressure. The experimental results were correlated with the modified and extended UNIQUAC models. The reliability of the experimental tie-line data was tested through the Othmer Tobias correlation equation. Distribution coefficients of dimethyl carbonate and diethyl carbonate were calculated from the experimental tie-line data and drawn. The temperature influence on liquid-phase equilibria was studied
